"recf7YV5yvbWuaVMt","target":"recJl6YAS1kSQ6t8W","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recv9Fwc46xLmKlb6","ref":"Acts.13.1","text":"Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers; as Barnabas, and Simeon that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene, and Manaen, which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.","year":45},{"id":"rechdBmPuF4pMCjig","ref":"Acts.13.2","text":"As they ministered to the Lord, and fasted, the Holy Ghost said, Separate me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have called them.","year":45},{"id":"recY88IFipSDXRPHt","ref":"Acts.13.3","text":"And when they had fasted and prayed, and laid their hands on them, they sent them away.","year":45},{"id":"rec9nLAJBnouNZSxT","ref":"Acts.13.4","text":"So they, being sent forth by the Holy Ghost, departed unto Seleucia; and from thence they sailed to Cyprus.","year":45},{"id":"recvo2pHYhE50X6v4","ref":"Acts.13.5","text":"And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they had also John to their minister.","year":45},{"id":"recMli10mS82DL4tc","ref":"Acts.13.6","text":"And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos, they found a certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew, whose name was Bar-jesus:","year":45},{"id":"rec29OikFdTirE0nc","ref":"Acts.13.7","text":"Which was with the deputy of the country, Sergius Paulus, a prudent man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God.","year":45},{"id":"recnUXfJdHA9EGTEf","ref":"Acts.13.8","text":"But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith.","year":45}]}
